ROSSLYN.

T HE Collegiate church of Rosslyn is situated on an elevated ground called the College Hill, overlooking the North Esk, about seven miles to the south of Edinburgh. It is a very common but popular error, even with writers like Sir lValter Scott, to speak of this charmingly decorated example of ecclesiastical architectum as merely a chapel.
